{"review": [{"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 0, "sentence": "The reinforcement learning tasks with sparse rewards are very important and challenging."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 1, "sentence": "The main idea of this work is to encourage intra-life novelty."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 2, "sentence": "The authors introduce the curiosity grid and the intrinsic reward term so that the agent can explore toward unvisited states at every episode."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 3, "sentence": "However, the results are not enough to be accepted to ICLR having a very high standard."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 4, "sentence": "In Section 3, the authors compare the game scores of DeepCS proposed in this paper only against to A2C."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 5, "sentence": "There are some RL algorithms reported to be better than A2C."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 6, "sentence": "For instance, I would like to see the comparison between DeepCS and SmartHash by Tang et al 2017."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 7, "sentence": "================================================================================================="}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 8, "sentence": "I've read the rebuttal. I updated my score but still not vote for accept."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 9, "sentence": "This paper is not my main research area."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 10, "sentence": "Very unfortunately, this paper was assigned to me."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 11, "sentence": "The main issue of this paper is the fair comparisons with other works."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 12, "sentence": "However, I don't have enough knowledges to judge this point."}, {"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 13, "sentence": "So please assess this paper with other reviewers comments."}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "S1ldJZzch7", "sid": 0, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondaryl